[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Deciding on setup for Neo4j**\n\nI need to decide on a deterministic setup for running queries with the Neo4j Java Driver. Normally, a Neo4j server is required, but meaningful coverage might still be achieved using a Docker image. Existing tests bypass the need for an external server, yet mapping failures might emerge without one. The prompt points to a library issue, and I have to consider if we should recommend Docker. There’s a possibility that concrete evidence, like a README example, might guide my choice.\n\n**Determining Docker setup for tests**\n\nI’m considering whether meaningful coverage is achievable. A generated test scaffold should exercise APIs, but if dealing with a database driver, Docker might be necessary. I need to figure out if I should recommend a Docker image and what the specific tag should be. The Neo4j server must be compatible with driver version 5.28.8. While the tests use Testcontainers, the artifact doesn’t seem to include that support, so I need to check if existing tests can work with Docker images.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ff4d9f20b4ae9ad016a429c5592c88196953b0903b362d2b6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQpxcw4EywKsP0yCdJouBsELADMhKRVqPnE0kIUccWVzoxtlRh6XwdPsWziJU5W6se6eP-RAJEa-b995oe12gtGFUZ0Th8Qku_hLNyddroWTFnmnmlJGt9-RUfoLri4lZzW6U4JO5OVZDxVYwU5vlFx1R8LOeh9FTC-IdH5-U5k1rAdVscsf9db2S2coN6HLt8W_iaxV-4r1prf3dyf6oKW01iq9DKid1kRL-3_AtRi6mZUBGiWKnTXtIAfVWq92kgCdKgnG7ImbWbp4RmBZyhdNkZ8aPfJx7Uc-D8EY8MOxQLPa99AtY0ULteeGiDC6UWKClsQKow1zd-XKS5obwpkK48yGBlOeisnjPA96AiNXnemt4arulL6F1jKLe2jSppwYK-nibyqer9RKz1_OkLnbbTRGa-1p-NbKhwB6H9UQfGofDRy9R1bMIe-CQmhmyVWZBQxQC0BU7Njlh1moMiznLMjjXOJNorr-fNQH6ZrGGeqiLCHQ_NMJL5eQA9VCcrPQ3HkgTRXo-axL7ua18ZwYFrOjaXrb2nFHhgW0sJrgpnRqovYspj4ziyDC9R9aKGsGzbh0PLbKSgqlTO4Yd45Ta-7lQRC2MOAUsBzNxXBEKVjBmyWSXwseqH01hjZ5mTRlXc2D6kkOkFHW_Hhcx-IEo0KR2yQR9GuAt-dxNzUBJ